cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with foundational results on the satisfiability problem in string logic with equations, regular membership and Presburger constraints over length functions. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with regular membership constraints in string logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with decision problems in string logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper provides a complexity analysis of the decision procedure. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with the worst-case complexity of the decision procedure.
